OL,6,FFrom 1945 to retirement in 1959,
OL,7,Fwithin the same university, he was the
OL,8,FMerton Professor of English Language
OL,9,Fand Literature and Fellow of Merton
OL,10,FCollege.
OL,12,FTolkien was a close friend of fellow
OL,13,Fauthor C. S. Lewis and co-member of
OL,14,Finformal literary discussion group The
OL,15,FInklings.
OL,17,FThough other authors had published
OL,18,Fworks of fantasy before Tolkien, the
OL,19,Fgreat success of The Hobbit followed
OL,20,Fby the huge impact of The Lord Of The
OL,21,FRings led to a resurgence of the genre.
